{"lemma":"عَيْرِ","slug":"عَيْرِ","root":"ع.#.ر","root_slug":"ع-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَيْرِ","root":"عير","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31189","n31190","n31196"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to denounce (someone) as dishonorable or shameful for (something), to shame; to defame; to besmirch; to stigmatize","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"أَعَيَّرْتَنِي قُرَّ الحَلَاءَةِ شَاتِيًا / وَأَنْتَ بِأَرْضٍ قُرُّهَا غَيْرُ مُنْجِمِ","english":"Shaming me, you say that I am wintering in woodlands / while you yourself are in a land with an unceasing chill!"},{"text":"عَيَّرَتْنِي بِٱلشَّيْبِ وَهُوَ وَقَارُ / لَيْتَهَا عَيَّرَتْ بِمَا هُوَ عَارُ","english":"She shamed me for my age, yet eld is reverence. / Would I be shamed for what is truly shameable!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to measure according to a set standard","tags":["obsolete","rare","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a caravan","tags":["collective","countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a donkey; a wild ass; an onager","tags":["countable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *ʕayr-."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31189","headword_ar":"عَيْرٌ","root":"Eyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K;) both the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"domestic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb;) its predominant application is to the former: (K:) so called because he goes away hither and thither ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiyru","text_ar":"يَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayatarad~adu","text_ar":"فَيَتَرَدَّدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") in the desert: (TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaArN","text_ar":"اَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K.) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaArN","text_ar":"عِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyuwrN","text_ar":"عُيُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyuwrapN","text_ar":"عُيُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyarapN","text_ar":"عِيَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwraA='u","text_ar":"مَعْيُورَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuwxaA='u","text_ar":"مَشْيُوخَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or this is [properly speaking] a quasi-pl. n., (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwraY","text_ar":"مَعْيُورَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also a quasipl. n.,] (Az, TA,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaraAtN","text_ar":"عِيَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaAraAtN","text_ar":"عِيَارَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [Dim."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyayorN","text_ar":"عُيَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. intra.] ―         -b2-  It is said in a prov., relating to contentment with that which is present and forgetting what is absent,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino *ahaba AlEayoru faEayorN fiY Alr~ibaATi","text_ar":"اـِنْ ذَهَبَ العَيْرُ فَعَيْرٌ فِى الرِّبَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If the ass has gone away, there is an ass in the tether"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A 'Obeyd.) ―         -b3-  You say also, of a place in which is no good,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kajawofi EayorK","text_ar":"هُوَ كَجَوْفِ عَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is like the belly of an ass"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kjwf AlEayori","text_ar":"كجوف العَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the belly of the ass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) because there is nothing in his belly of which any use is made: (S, TA:) or this originated from the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^axolaY mino jawofi","text_ar":"هُوَ اَخْلَى مِنْ جَوْفِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaArK","text_ar":"حِمَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is more empty than the valley of Himar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, * TA;) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmAr","text_ar":"حمار"},{"kind":"text","text":"was the name of a certain unbeliever, who possessed a valley, which for his infidelity, God rendered waste and unproductive; (O, * TA;) and Imra-el-Keys, (O, TA,) as some say, but correctly Taäbbata-sharrà, (O,) quoting the above-mentioned saying, has substituted"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEyr","text_ar":"العير"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmAr","text_ar":"حمار"},{"kind":"text","text":", for the sake of the metre. (O, TA.) ―         -b4-  One says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*al~u mina AlEayori","text_ar":"اَذَلُّ مِنَ العَيْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More vile than the ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [But this is doubtful: see the same phrase expl. differently later in this paragraph. The wild ass is superior to every other kind of animal that is an object of the chase: (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraA^N","text_ar":"فَرَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and hence, app., the signification here next following.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayorN","text_ar":"عَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) of a people: (S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaArN","text_ar":"اَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) ―         -b6-  The saying (S, K) of the people of Syria, used by them proverbially, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayorN","text_ar":"عَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEayorK waziyaAdapu Ea$arapK","text_ar":"بِعَيْرٍ وَزِيَادَةُ عَشَرَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord for a lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord"},{"kind":"text","text":"is succeeded"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a lord, and an increase of ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is expl. by the fact that, when the Khaleefeh of the sons of Umeiyeh died, and another arose, he increased their stipends by ten dirhems: (S, O, K:) so they said thus on that occasion. (O, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayoru Als~araApi","text_ar":"عَيْرُ السَّرَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the pigeon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"short in the legs, which are coved with feathers, yellow in the legs and bill, having the eye bordered with black, of a clear colour inclining to greenness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow in the belly and the part beneath its wings and the inner part of its tail; as though it were a variegated"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burod","text_ar":"بُرْد"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euyuwru Als~araApi","text_ar":"عُيُورُ السَّرَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~araApu","text_ar":"السَّرَاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a place in the district of Et-Táïf: they assert that this bird eats three hundred figs, from the time of their coming forth from among the leaves, small; and in like manner, grapes. (TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridge, in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the iron head"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2209},{"kind":"text","text":"or blade of an arrow or of a spear or of a sword or of a knife or the like. (S, O.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a little wall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a leaf; its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle rib."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent part, in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the scapula, or shoulderblade. (S, O.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"projecting, bone in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the hand: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaArN","text_ar":"اَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [In the K, it is expl. simply by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaZomu Aln~aAtiy^u","text_ar":"العَظْمُ النَّاتِيُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasaTahaA","text_ar":"وَسَطَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this is a wrong reading, app. occasioned by an omission, which is supplied in the TA, though somewhat awkwardly: it seems that we should read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamina Alkaf~i AlEaZomu Aln~atiy^u wasaTahaA","text_ar":"وَمِنَ الكَفِّ العَظْمُ النَّتِيُ وَسَطَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, more probably,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wmn Alkatifi Alx","text_ar":"ومن الكَتِفِ الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for I incline to think that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkf~","text_ar":"الكفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the TA is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alktf","text_ar":"الكتف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the last signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":", given here, is doubtful.] ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberance, in the upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"convex, part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the foot. (S, O, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant, bone in the body."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ridge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a rock,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"naturally prominent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant, in an even thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of an even thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surface"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Each of the two portions of flesh and sinew next the back bone, one on either side thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"both together are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayoraAni","text_ar":"عَيْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.) [So called because it forms a kind of ridge.] ―         -b10-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant, part at the pupil"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buw^obuw^","text_ar":"بُوْبُو"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lid"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the eye: (S, O, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner angle"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^`qiY","text_ar":"مَاٰقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the CK, I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oqaY","text_ar":"مَاْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in other copies of the K,] of the eye: (Th, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"image that is seen in the black of the eye when a thing faces it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Tálib, L, K; *) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEobapN","text_ar":"لُعْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Aboo-Tálib, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye-ball:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a looking from the outer angle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHoZ","text_ar":"لَحْظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or perhaps this signifies here the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outer angle itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Hence the saying, (S, O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalotu *aAka","text_ar":"فَعَلْتُ ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabola EayorK wamaA jaraY","text_ar":"قَبْلَ عَيْرٍ وَمَا جَرَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did that before a look from the outer angle of the eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before he winked"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"could wink"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the “ image that is seen in the black of the eye; ” and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA jrY","text_ar":"ما جرى"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ what moved, ” i. e., “ the eye itself: ” (Aboo-Tálib:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before I looked"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"could look"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not used with a negative: (Th:) nor do you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu *Ak","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fElt","text_ar":"فعلت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*Ak","text_ar":"ذاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this phrase]: (A O, S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"here signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuka qabola","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُكَ قَبْلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayorK wamaA jaraY","text_ar":"عَيْرٍ وَمَا جَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee before a sleeper awoke"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"could awake"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AA, TA.) ―         -b11-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watid","text_ar":"وَتِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tragus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is in the inner part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the ear: (S:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watidN","text_ar":"وَتِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the interior of the ear which is below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroE","text_ar":"فَرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper portion thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) in a man and in a horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayor","text_ar":"عَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of an arrow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayoraAni","text_ar":"عَيْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"matonaAni","text_ar":"مَتْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two backs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though the word may have some other application in this case,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the two ears"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaArN","text_ar":"عِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden pin, peg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stake, which is fixed in the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a wall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) Hence, as some say, the prov."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^a*al~u mina","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَذَلُّ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayori","text_ar":"العَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is more vile than the wooden pin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peg, of a tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) [See another explanation above: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*al~apN","text_ar":"مَذَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Hence also, accord. to some, (TA,) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^adoriY A^aY~u mano","text_ar":"مَا اَدْرِى اَىُّ مَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba AlEayora huwa","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ العَيْرَ هُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I known not what one of mankind is he."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, O, K, TA.) And hence too, as some say, the saying of El-Hárith Ibn-Hillizeh, (O, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"zaEamuwA A^an~a kul~a mano Daraba AlEayo\n                      \n                     \n                        ra mawaAlK lanaA waA^an~aA AlwalaA='u"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which Aboo-'Amr Ibn-El-'Alà said that he had passed away, or died, who knew the meaning of this verse, (S, O, TA,) and which is differently related, some saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAlK lahaA","text_ar":"مَوَالٍ لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and some saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwilaA='u","text_ar":"الوِلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) but various meanings are assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEyr","text_ar":"العير"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance; and some expl. it as a proper name: (O, TA:) and some, relating this verse, say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEiyra","text_ar":"العِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (TA:) [the following explanation of the verse has been given as preferable to others:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the Arákim, mentioned two verses before,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have asserted that all who have hunted the wild ass are the sons of our paternal uncles, and that we are the relations"},{"kind":"text","text":"of them;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwlA='","text_ar":"الولا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoHaAbu walaAy^ihimo","text_ar":"اَصْحَابُ وَلَايِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": meaning that we are responsible for their crimes, or offences, as though we were their heirs. (EM p. 261.)       -A4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain piece of wood which is in the fore part of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehicle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawodaj","text_ar":"هَوْدَج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)       -A5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A drum."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) And so, as some say, in the verse cited above. (O, TA.)       -A6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain of El-Medeeneh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and, as some say, of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain of Mekkeh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aEoyaAru","text_ar":"الاَعْيَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(of which the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayoru","text_ar":"العَيْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA) is a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain bright stars in the track of the feet of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suhayol","text_ar":"سُهَيْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Canopus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","O","Az","AA","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n31190","headword_ar":"عِيرٌ","root":"Eyr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A caravan;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAfilapN","text_ar":"قَافِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of the fem. gen.: (K:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he journeyed: ” (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels that carry provision of corn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K:) then generally applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any caravan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a caravan of asses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then extended to any caravan; as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayorN","text_ar":"عَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being originally and regularly of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEulN","text_ar":"فُعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyurN","text_ar":"عُيُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suqufN","text_ar":"سُقُفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqofN","text_ar":"سَقْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) but it has no proper sing.: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any beasts upon which provision of corn is brought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mules:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned in the Kur xii. 94 consisted of asses; and the assertion of him who says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied specially to camels is false: (AHeyth, O, TA:) Nuseyr cites the poet Aboo-'Amr El-Asadee as applying this appellation to asses; and says that camels are not so called unless employed for bringing provision of corn: (AHeyth, TA:) IAar says that it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels bearing burdens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not bearing burdens:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az:) but camels are not thus called that bring corn for their owners: (TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikaAb","text_ar":"رِكَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaraAtN","text_ar":"عِيَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is of the fem. gender, and, being a subst., with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"movent, accord. to the dial. of Hudheyl, for they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawozaAtN","text_ar":"جَوْزَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaAtN","text_ar":"بَيْضَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyoraAtN","text_ar":"عِيْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) is allowable, (S,) and is the regular form, and occurs in a trad., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels carrying merchandise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Mgh","O","Msb","AHeyth","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n31196","headword_ar":"عَيِّرٌ","root":"Eyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^irN","text_ar":"عَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}